:69:"Bridge increase leg strength glute activationa dn decrease back pain.";i:45;s:58:"Hold the chair or the armrest with your hands for support.";i:46;s:57:"Lean back about 45 degreesor as much as the chair allows.";i:47;s:34:"Pull your legs towards your chest.";i:48;s:41:"Extend your legs straight out in the air.";i:49;s:97:"Pull your legs back again towards your chest then drop your feet without them touching the floor.";i:50;s:29:"Repeat the exercise 20 times.";i:51;s:113:"Cross your top leg over the bottom leg bending at the knee so that your top foot is in front of your bottom knee.";i:52;s:74:"Lift your bottom leg toward the ceiling in a slow and controlled movement.";i:53;s:54:"Chair Workout for Legs Single Leg Squats on the Chair.";i:54;s:128:"Start standing close to the edge of the chair then balance on your RIGHT leg with your left leg slightly lifted in front of you.";i:55;s:116:"Lower yourself down as if you were sitting onto the chair but then press into your RIGHT heel to come right back up.";i:56;s:67:"Repeat for 15 repetitions on with your RIGHT leg then switch sides.";i:57;s:86:"The good old squat is the best exercise for toning the legs and the entire lower body.";i:58;s:73:"It engages and tones to glutes quads and hamstrings all at the same time.";i:59;s:98:"The inclusion of a chair in this exercise helps to ensure a full range of motion and perfect form.";i:60;s:84:"The chair squat is a wonderful chair based exercise for those who are new to squats.";i:61;s:13:"HOW TO DO IT.";i:62;s:56:"Sit tall in your chair with your feet flat on the floor.";i:63;s:72:"Contract your abdominal muscles and lift your right thigh off the chair.";i:64;s:109:"Lift it as high as you can without your lower back rounding pause for a moment then lower your leg back down.";i:65;s:49:"How to Get a Full-Body Workout With Just a Chair.";i:66;s:175:"Try several different exercises to start with 20 to 30 reps per exercise and gradually increase the number of exercises reps and total workout time as your endurance improves.";i:67;s:176:"Simple air-punching with or without hand weights is an easy cardio exercise from a seated position and can be fun when playing along with a Nintendo Wii or Xbox 360 video game.";i:68;s:94:"Sit up straight in your chair and hold a medicine ball basketball or balloon up to your chest.";i:69;s:80:"The more you squeeze the ball the harder you will be working your chest muscles.";i:70;s:131:"Push the ball out in front of you until your elbows are nearly straight and continue to squeeze the ball and work the chest muscle.";}}